    • equals

      public boolean equals(@Nullable Object obj)
      Description copied from class: JvmTypeOrVoid
      Whether given object is equal to this type. Two types are equal if their representation in the bytecode is identical, i.e. both JvmTypeOrVoid.nonGenericString() and JvmTypeOrVoid.genericString() return the same value. Note, that equal types may have different sets of type annotations applied.
